<div class="res-text richtextContent background-opaque" id="c819392b-65a3-4b2b-b427-52abe39a8928" >

    <p>"As faculty members and instructors, you are in a strong position to role model qualities and behaviours inherent to academic integrity. Your actions provide a clear message to students, about our standards and expectations. Faculty members are in a unique position to influence students from the first class."</p> 
<p><strong><a href="https://www.ryerson.ca/academicintegrity">Visit the Academic Integrity Office (AIO) to learn more</a></strong>.</p> 
<p>If you administer exams in classrooms with tiered seating, you may find these tips to be helpful.&nbsp;</p> 
<p><a href="/content/dam/learning-teaching/teaching-resources/assessment/tiered-seating-academic-integrity.pdf"><span class="sr-only">PDF file</span><strong>Best Practices: Tiered Seating and Academic Integrity</strong><span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-file-pdf-o"></span></a></p>
    





